summary: In Week 10 of the NFL season, Detroit Lions quarterback Jared Goff had a rollercoaster performance. Despite throwing a career-high 5 interceptions, Goff also led the Lions to a 26-23 victory over the Houston Texans. Statistically, Goff's 5 interceptions were a remarkable feat, as only 1-in-780,000 quarterbacks have thrown 5 or more interceptions in a game. Despite his costly turnovers, Goff's resilience and the Lions' strong defensive performance ultimately secured the win. Fantasy football analysts are projecting Goff to score modest points in upcoming games, given his recent struggles. However, some experts believe that Goff's stats, including his close connection with wide receiver Amon-Ra St. Brown, could potentially lead to an impressive 2024 NFL MVP campaign.
